1️⃣ INSTITUTIONAL STABILITY
Purpose
Measure execution consistency across time and cohorts.

1.1 Stability Index (Core Metric)
Composite 0–100 index.
Derived from normalized variance of:
    • % Raw Marks variance (across runs)
    • % Accuracy variance
    • Phase adherence variance
    • Discipline Index variance
    • Risk state fluctuation score
Formula Concept
stabilityIndex =
100 - weightedVarianceScore
Lower variance → higher stability.

UI Components
    • Large numeric display (0–100)
    • Gauge chart
    • 12-month trend line
Under it:
Stable above 75
Watch zone 60–75
Unstable below 60
Not judgmental — purely diagnostic.

1.2 Performance Variability
Charts:
    • Std deviation of % Raw Marks (timeline)
    • Std deviation of % Accuracy
    • Batch-to-batch spread comparison
    • Stability vs Difficulty level heatmap
Purpose:
Identify systemic volatility.

1.3 Template Stability Comparison
When same template used multiple times:
Show:
    • % Raw delta across runs
    • % Accuracy delta
    • Risk shift across batches
Interpretation logic:
    • Stable template + unstable batch → training issue
    • Unstable template + stable batch → template issue

